text: Woolsey Creek is a stream in Camden and Laclede counties the Ozarks of south central Missouri. Woolsey Creek is a tributary to the Niangua River. The stream enters the Niangua just upstream (south) of Lake Niangua.Hahatonka, Missouri, 7.5 Minute Topographic Quadrangle, USGS, 1982 The stream headwaters are at and the confluence with the Niangua is at . Woolsey Creek was named after Daniel Woolsey, a pioneer citizen. ==See also== *List of rivers of Missouri ==References== Category:Rivers of Camden County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Laclede County, Missouri Category:Rivers of Missouri
